The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 22 September is 73,765 (8,501.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 17 September, there were 1,490 new confirmed cases (171.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 10 September, there were 1,984 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 25% (494 fewer cases).
